The paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for relation extraction in biological text. Specifically, it proposes a model that uses self-attention to simultaneously predict relationships between all mention pairs in a document. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of Computation and Language (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of multi-instance learning and weakly labeled data, which are techniques commonly used in Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) respectively.
